Description: Ostracon, small fragment of the body of a red pottery vessel, the fabric is grey in section, the interior is ribbed and partially covered with a glossy yellow-brown resinous deposit, the exterior is covered with a self-slip and remains of three lines of black-painted demotic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393792) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393792)
